"Join us for a 1h 15m practical, hands-on session where four library consortia: Consortium of Swiss Academic Libraries (CSAL), Jisc, Lyrasis, and Sikt share how they fund and support open infrastructure. This session will provide real, actionable insight into different models for how consortia manage investment in open science services.

Each consortium will present its approach, followed by a Q &amp; A session where you can ask direct questions. Whether you're exploring how to get started or looking to strengthen existing support, this session is designed to help you take the next step. What you’ll learn&nbsp;

You'll leave this session with a clearer understanding of how library consortia organize funding for open infrastructure, practical strategies you can bring back to your own consortium or institution, and knowledge of funding pathways."

"We’re happy to share reports from three more projects strengthening the quality and sustainability of no-fee open access (OA) journals in Africa.&nbsp;

Together, the three projects strengthen a total of seven journals – five in Ghana and two in South Africa. The projects were among 17 in nine countries that were awarded grants in 2024 through the three-year project,&nbsp;‘Collaboration for Sustainable Open Access Publishing in Africa', funded by Wellcome. The grants specifically target no-fee OA (also known as Diamond OA) journals and journal platforms. Diamond OA means that the journals do not charge any fees for publishing or reading articles....

